      "content": "hey, i'm working on this medical NLP project and i need a python function for a dependency parser. it doesnt have to be super high performance, just needs to be able to extract head-child relations. \n\ni have this specific sentence from one of our clinical notes that i need to parse correctly for my pipeline: \"Patient exhibits acute respiratory distress.\"\n\nhere is the structure i need the function to return for that sentence:\n{'Patient': 'ROOT', 'exhibits': 'Patient', 'acute': 'distress', 'respiratory': 'distress', 'distress': 'exhibits'}\n\ncan u write a function `get_dependencies(sentence: str) -> dict` that handles this? i'll run it against some tests to make sure the format is right.",
