      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is a Python function using the spaCy library to achieve the dependency parsing and return the structure you specified. Since spaCy's raw output needs transformation, the function iterates through the tokens and maps the head-child relationships into a dictionary format. Using spaCy is a standard and effective way to handle this type of NLP task.\n\n```python\nimport spacy\n\n# Load the English model (ensure you have run: python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm)\nnlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n\ndef get_dependencies(sentence: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Parses a sentence and returns a dictionary mapping children to their heads.\"\"\"\n    doc = nlp(sentence)\n    dependency_map = {}\n    for token in doc:\n        # Store the relationship from the token (child) to its head\n        dependency_map[token.text] = token.head.text\n    return dependency_map\n\n# Test case\nsentence = \"Patient exhibits acute respiratory distress.\"\nresult = get_dependencies(sentence)\nprint(result)\n```",
